!begin_node v_offset

(!begin_liste) [Availability]

!item [Name:]
ØSet screen offsetÆ - Set the top screen margin.

!item [Opcode:]
5 (Escape 101)

!item [Syntax:]
void v_offset ( int16_t handle, int16_t offset );

!item [Description:]
The call v_offset sets the offset in raster lines to the start of the logical
screen. The following apply:

!begin_xlist !short [Parameter]
!item [Parameter]
Meaning
!item [~]
~
!item [handle]
Workstation identifier
!item [offset]
Number of raster lines below the top screen edge up to the start of the
logical screen
!end_xlist

(!B)Note:(!b) The function is described in (!I)no official(!i) documentation -
use it at your own risk!
               
!item [(!nolink [Return]) value:]
The function does not return a result.

!item [Availability:]
ROM screen driver.

!item [Group:]
Special functions

!item [See also:]
(!link [Binding] [Bindings for v_offset])

(!ende_liste)
!end_node



!begin_node Bindings for v_offset
!ignore_index

(!begin_liste) [GEM-Arrays]

!item [C:]
void v_offset ( int16_t handle, int16_t offset );

!item [Binding:]
!begin_verbatim
void v_offset (int16_t handle, int16_t offset)
{
   intin[0] = offset;

   contrl[0] = 5;
   contrl[1] = 0;
   contrl[3] = 1;
   contrl[5] = 101;
   contrl[6] = handle;

   vdi ();
}
!end_verbatim

